Example:
A custom tag in JSP has an attribute pos="10"
the setter in java is:
public void setPos(String sPos)
{
 this.nPos = (new Integer(sPos)).intValue();
}
and the getter
public int getPos() 
{
 return this.nPos;
}

This works well for sometime until one day Tomcat throws an Exception because 
the method setPos(int) was called. Then the setter setPos(int) must be created

If this is not a bug please tell me how can I find out what setter will Tomcat 
call

it calls:
public void setPos(int nPos)
{
  this.nPos = nPos;
}

 The problem is that tomcat decides after some time that is better to call the 
setter with int and not the one wiht String
 It is unpleasant to see that after two weeks of using a JSP page you get an 
error because the setter(the one tomcat wants) is not found
